subSection.paragraph:
We inferred a maximum likelihood (ML) phylogenetic tree for the min187 dataset using RAxML v.8.2.12 ( Stamatakis 2014 ) by creating 1000 ML trees under the GTR + Gamma model (seed 260697) as chosen by ModelTestNG (
Darriba et al. 2020
) with the outgroup set to
P. omiscomaycus
. Support for our maximum likelihood tree was obtained from 1000 bootstraps run on the highest likelihood tree using RAxML (seed 345188). We then visualized the tree in iTOL V5 ( Letunic & Bork 2021 ). Bayesian clustering inference was done using unlinked loci from our min186 data set on structure_threader (
Pina-Martins et al. 2017
) and STRUCTURE v. 2.3.4 (
Pritchard et al. 2000
) using default settings. We ran three replicates of each K value from 1 to 20 for the dataset. Each STRUCTURE analysis was then run for 1 x 107 iterations, with the addition of a burn-in of 2.5 x 106 . To determine inferred K values from the STRUCTURE analysis, we visually observed each resulting run and did not count populations with membership of less than 0.001 as inferred K. Results were then pooled by observed population membership. This observed membership was then used to estimate log likelihood. We then estimated pairwise F ST ( Weir & Cockerham 1984 ) between these clusters using the R package Hierfstat ( Goudet 2005 ) on the same unlinked loci as our STRUCTURE analysis.

