Cloaca located immediately anterior to the anal fin origin, though migrates as the fish matures (
Mansueti 1963
).

Lateral line usually incomplete, many sensory pores on head as well as several rows of external neuromasts on the dorsal surface of the snout, and many external neuromast patches under the lower jaw. The sensory system has been covered thoroughly in Moore and Burris (
Moore & Burris 1956
).

subSection.paragraph:
In this study we reexamined relationships within
Aphredoderus
. We found higher than expected species diversity within
Aphredoderus
. Early taxonomic work recognized two distinct subspecific forms(
Jordan & Evermann 1896
). Subsequent work by Boltz and Stauffer (1993) supported this assessment and suggested a wide zone of intergradation ranging from the Pascagoula River in Mississippi to the Satilla River in Georgia . Similar distribution patterns of lowland fishes present from the Mississippi River to the Atlantic slope generally does not support widespread intergrade zones within this region ( Bermingham & Avise 1986 ;
Brownstein et al. 2022
; Gilbert & Bailey 1972 ;
Hunt et al. 2021
;
Kim et al. 2022
). The zone of intergradation proposed for
Aphredoderus
was much wider than that proposed for other taxa. Our analyses suggest that rather than a zone of intergradation, there is a mosaic of distinct species with overlapping ranges.
